"""
=============================================================================
APEX Q — HIGH-IMPACT DoD CONTRACT TRACKER
=============================================================================

Captures DoD contract actions with the financial scale to move a public stock,
maps them to tickers, and scores them for stock impact.

ARCHITECTURE NOTE — read this before changing anything:

  defense.gov is the SIGNAL. USAspending is the BACKFILL.

  The DoD posts awards at 5:00pm ET the day they happen. USAspending publishes
  the same award as structured data weeks later. If you ingest for alpha from
  USAspending you are systematically late to every single trade. So:

    defense.gov 5pm  -> same-day detection, thin data, regex-parsed
    USAspending      -> T+days enrichment: UEI, CAGE, NAICS, competition,
                        obligated vs ceiling, place of performance
    SAM.gov          -> forward-looking: RFPs and pre-solicitations, i.e. the
                        contract that has not been awarded yet

  Each source writes into the same `dod_contracts` table, keyed on a stable
  hash, and later sources ENRICH rows the earlier ones created.

VALUE FLOOR:

  $100M, tested against max(obligated, ceiling). A $9B IDIQ ceiling with a $2M
  initial obligation is exactly the announcement we exist to catch -- filtering
  on obligated alone would throw it away. Both are stored; both are tested.

=============================================================================
"""

